message: Even as Williams was penning her book, she had no idea that her home state of Florida was ranked No. 3 in the U.S. — surpassed only by California and Texas — for reports of suspected human trafficking, according to the National Human Trafficking Resource Center.

data.description: “I always wanted to be a faith-based novelist,” recalled Yvonne Williams, co-pastor with husband, Marion, of the new Ascension Hill church in Inglis.
data.title: Two local pastors at forefront of educating public on human trafficking
